    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="617"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d617">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Pera</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 9, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>At Beirut and Alexandretta to interchange, and one always at Mersine.
                    Missionaries report that the presence of <hi rend="italic">Marblehead</hi>
                    prevented massacre at Adana. They beg that a light-armed dispatch bark will be
                    kept at Constantinople. Every great power has one here. A revolution is
                    preparing in Macedonia. Turkish garrison of 400 killed and captured at
                    Zeitoun.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
